<br>
You would need to define 'best' here very carefully. As far as nukes go, I would contend your statement to be entirely incorrect.<br>
<br>
As stated on the Spells forum in the thread about Sirocco vs SOFB, Sirocco has in practice a DPM of 4.42 for an Evocation Mage, which includes resists. From theory alone, Seukors, also evocation, for an Evocation Mage, with the standard damage bracer, has a DPM of 4.40, but this is 'perfect', and would be reduced in practice by resists.<br>
<br>
By comparison, SOFB, for a Conjuration Mage, with the standard damage bracer, has a DPM of 4.14, but this is 'perfect', and would be reduced in practice by resists.<br>
<br>
Yes, SOFB is a simple DD so requires far less skill to use than Sirocco or Seukors, but in damage output terms, it is considerably inferior to the best Evocation nukes. Add to this that you use Scintillation in AE groups (evocation), and Sigil for fast casts (also evocation), and it should be clear to anyone other than the most blinkered, for nuking alone, Evocation &gt; Conjuration, even at 60.<br>
<br>
The other factors, tho, I'd agree with, so overall, if you raid more, conjuration is still the better choice, for all the well known reasons. But to me, since I style myself a damage dealer, they are less important, so I remain Evocation.<br>
<br>
